=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0I just got an email back
from Jason at beetles-uk.com. He states that the Type 2's are 100%new,
built in Brasil and then converted in the UK. They are fuel injected
1600cc with catalytic converter. After a quick currency conversion, it
appears that the price quoted for the Rio Camper is approximately
$19,250.00 before shipping from the UK, so they are not exactly cheap to
say the least. I am not sure of availability of parts ('79 spec?). 
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0Perhaps if a few listees
got together and did a group purchase we could get a better price from
the dealer and do a consolidated shipment in a 40' container ( I think 6
Type 2's should fit in a normal shipping container). 
